### **3. 27_LogSurgeDetector**  
**Description:**  
Scans logs and finds spikes in error or warning messages over time.

#### **README.md**
```markdown
# LogSurgeDetector - Log Spike Finder

LogSurgeDetector analyzes logs for bursts of activity, often signaling bugs, attacks, or system failures.

## Features
- Detects time-based clusters  
- Supports multiple log types  
- Outputs visual frequency summary  

## Usage
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/27_LogSurgeDetector.git
cd 27_LogSurgeDetector
python analyze.py /var/log/syslog
